titleStmt.title: The seamans protestation. Concerning their ebbing and flowing to and from the Parliament House, at Westminster: upon Tuesday the 11. day of Ianuary. 1642. Ordered, by the Vice-Admiral, to be published and set forth throughout the whole kingdome, as a manifestation of the seamans loyaltie to their king, and love to their country.

notesStmt.note: Reproduction of the original in the British Library.
